A United-Kingdom (UK)-based Nigerian philanthropist, Cap­tain Mother Olufunmilayo Hasson, is set to launch the Captain Mother Olufunmilayo Hasson Foundation for the sole purpose of taking care of the under-privileged. Chairman of the Central Planning Committee, James Oyeleke, said the commis­sioning, which is going to be a three-in-one event, will take place on Saturday, April 16, 2022, at the Lagos State Chamber of Commerce, Mar­wa Garden, Lagos. The event will feature launch of books, conferment of award and an endowment fund of two hundred and fifty million naira to support the foundation. Oyeleke said the event would be attended by digni­taries in the society includ­ing Sir Adebukunola Aebutu Kessington, who will chair the day with the Executive Governor of Lagos State, Ba­bajide Sanwo-Olu, is the chief host.